    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This issue is really old, but has good SEO. I'm adding on here a possible new case where rootPath will behave wrongly (in v4):\r\n\r\n1. have a hierarchical refinement on the page which is not the root refinement\r\n2. add a hierarchical menu with a rootPath to the page\r\n3. notice it does not take the rootPath in account, and keeps the old refinement\r\n\r\nThis happens because we might not be calling `.make` on `SearchParameters` (only place where rootPath \"exists\" / is put back where something else is refined).\r\n\r\nThis bug is mostly hypothetical, and should be confirmed if someone has it",
